'''Almond''' is an [[unincorporated community]] in [[Swain County, North Carolina|Swain County]], [[North Carolina]], [[United States]]. Almond is located on the [[Little Tennessee River]] and [[North Carolina Highway 28]] {{convert|7.9|mi|km}} west-southwest of [[Bryson City, North Carolina|Bryson City]]. Almond has a [[post office]] with [[ZIP code]] 28702, which opened on March 17, 1886.{{GR|7}}<ref>{{cite web|title=Postmaster Finder - Post Offices by ZIP Code|url=http://webpmt.usps.gov/pmt008.cfm|publisher=[[United States Postal Service]]|accessdate=March 11, 2013}}</ref> The community was named for Bud Almond, who provided the land on which the town was founded.<ref name="gnis"/>

